  <formalMetadata>
    <description>Document containing a link; when the link is activated a MIDI file is loaded.</description>
    <title>Change of user agent when a link is activated [new]</title>
    <dc:creator>johannes.koch@fit.fraunhofer.de</dc:creator>
    <dc:language>en</dc:language>
    <dc:rights>Copyright BenToWeb 2004-2007</dc:rights>
    <date>2007-12-07</date>
    <status>draft</status>
  </formalMetadata>
  <technology>
    <recommendation xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/">
      <label><html:acronym>XHTML</html:acronym>â„¢ 1.0 The Extensible HyperText Markup Language (Second Edition)</label>
      <testElements>
        <testElement>
          <elementName localname="a" namespace="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>
          <specReference xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/TR/1999/REC-html401-19991224/struct/links.html#edef-A"/>
        </testElement>
      </testElements>
    </recommendation>
  </technology>
  <testCase complexity="atomic">
    <purpose>
      <p>The test is intended to pass because when the link is activated a new user agent is launched (media player) and a midi file is played.</p>
    </purpose>
        <expertGuidance>
            <p>Check whether there is any change of context when the link is activated.</p>
        </expertGuidance>
    <requiredTests>
      <testModes>
        <testMode>oneExpert</testMode>
      </testModes>
    </requiredTests>
    <files>
      <file hrefLang="en" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc3.2.1_l1_009.html"/>
    </files>
  </testCase>
  <rules>
    <rule id="http://bentoweb.org/refs/rulesets.xml#WCAG2_20070517_3.2_consistent-behavior-receive-focus" primary="yes">
      <locations expectedResult="pass">
        <location column="62" line="7" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:p/h:a"/>
      </locations>
      <functionalOutcome>
        <p>Change of user agent when the link is activated.</p>
      </functionalOutcome>
      <techComment>
        <p>The activation of the link causes the browser to load a resource, that the browser is not able to handle natively.</p>
        <p>This test case maps to technique <html:span class="technique"><html:a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2007/WD-WCAG20-TECHS-20070517/#G107">G107: Using "activate" rather than "focus" as a trigger for changes of context</html:a></html:span>.</p>
      </techComment>
    </rule>
  </rules>
  <namespaceMappings>
    <namespace nsPrefix="h" nsURI="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>
  </namespaceMappings>
</testCaseDescription>

